title: Bug 121170 - get column label from meta data object should return some user recognizable strings
OB: When calling IMetaData.getColumnLabel() before data extraction, the method does not return any recognizable strings.
EB: The method IMetaData.getColumnLabel() should return user recognizable strings, even before data extraction.
SR:
To reproduce the issue, follow these steps:
1. Call IMetaData.getColumnLabel() before data extraction.
2. Verify that the returned value is not a recognizable string.
3. Call IMetaData.getColumnLabel() after data extraction.
4. Verify that the returned value is a recognizable string.
